<header>
  <h1>TTT</h1>
  <p>Tri-Tetra Symmetry Model</p>
</header>

<section id="overview">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    A geometric model describing how symmetry and balance generate stable structures.
    The center is not predefined — it emerges from equilibrium.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="core">
  <h2>Core Theorem</h2>
  <div class="equation">
    \[ v_1 + v_2 + v_3 + v_4 = 0 \]
  </div>
  <p>
    This condition produces a tetrahedral configuration with equal angles (~109.47°).
  </p>
</section>

<section id="geometry">
  <h2>Geometry</h2>
  <p>
    3 → triangle<br>
    4 → tetrahedron<br>
    dual → octahedron<br>
    limit → sphere
  </p>

  <div class="diagram">
    <!-- simple tetrahedron projection -->
    <svg width="200" height="200">
      <circle cx="100" cy="40" r="4" fill="#58a6ff"/>
      <circle cx="40" cy="160" r="4" fill="#58a6ff"/>
      <circle cx="160" cy="160" r="4" fill="#58a6ff"/>
      <circle cx="100" cy="110" r="4" fill="#58a6ff"/>

      <line x1="100" y1="40" x2="40" y2="160" stroke="#aaa"/>
      <line x1="100" y1="40" x2="160" y2="160" stroke="#aaa"/>
      <line x1="40" y1="160" x2="160" y2="160" stroke="#aaa"/>
      <line x1="100" y1="40" x2="100" y2="110" stroke="#aaa"/>
      <line x1="40" y1="160" x2="100" y2="110" stroke="#aaa"/>
      <line x1="160" y1="160" x2="100" y2="110" stroke="#aaa"/>
    </svg>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="spectrum">
  <h2>Spectrum</h2>
  <div class="equation">
    \[ j_1(z) = 0 \]
    \[ z_1 \approx 4.4934,\; z_2 \approx 7.7252,\; z_3 \approx 10.9041 \]
  </div>
  <p>
    These define discrete spherical modes.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="hypothesis">
  <h2>Hypothesis</h2>
  <p>
    These modes may correspond to hierarchical structures in physics.
    This interpretation remains unverified.
  </p>
</section>

<footer>
  <p>github.com/kiki054-n/TTT</p>
</footer>

